The paper deals with compressed sensing and convex optimization, which are core topics in information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The Lasso and Dantzig selector models are popular in statistics (cs.ST) and data science (cs.DS). The paper also involves numerical analysis (cs.NA) and signal processing (cs.SI) in the context of compressed sensing.
